The paper deals with online computation and optimization problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of advice, which is a form of pre-processing, also relates to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The specific problems studied, such as bin packing and scheduling, are common topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
